------------------------------------------------------------------------------
README file for KMATH_FFT3D
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

VERSION 1.0 : Dec. 20, 2014

KMATH_FFT3D is the 3D-FFT API for cubic-distributed data.

KMATH_RANDOM is Open Source Software (OSS).
See the copyright form 'LICENCE.txt'.


Getting Started

1) Do configure.

  % ./configure

  If you need to compile it on a cross-compiling environment,
  set up appropriate compiler options and configure options.

  Followings are example on K computer
  % export FC=mpifrtpx  
  % export FCFLAGS='-Kopenmp -Cpp -Kfast'  
  % export F77=mpifrtpx  
  % export FFLAGS='-Kopenmp -Cpp -Kfast'  
  % export LDFLAGS='-Kopenmp'
  % ./configure --host=K

  Followings are example on a general PC cluster with Intel compiler
  % export FC=mpif90  
  % export FCFLAGS='-openmp -fpp -O3 -Free'  
  % export F77=mpif90  
  % export FFLAGS='-openmp -fpp -O3 -Free  
  % export LDFLAGS='-openmp'
  % ./configure 

  If something troubls happen when you do the configure script,
  please run the script auto.sh beforehand.

2) Do make, then libkmath_fft_3d.a will be build.

  % make


For bug report or additional information,
please contact the corresponding developper.

